We can differentiate the geometric series with respect to x, which gives us \[\frac{d}{dx} \left( \frac{1}{1 - \frac{1}{x}} \right) = \frac{1}{(x-1)^2}.\] Therefore, we have that \[ S(x) = \frac{\frac{1}{x}}{(x-1)^2} \] valid when \(|x| > 1\).
